WEBVTT

00:06.789 --> 00:09.096
- [screaming]
- Jill, Jill, look at me.

00:10.227 --> 00:10.271
You gotta do everything
I tell you to.

00:10.836 --> 00:11.837
Three, two, one.

00:11.881 --> 00:15.624
[sinister music]

00:15.667 --> 00:17.408
- It's not Tom's.

00:17.452 --> 00:19.236
- No, he just wanted it to be.

00:19.280 --> 00:21.499
- What matters is that he lied.
- You tamed it.

00:21.543 --> 00:24.459
Your stuff, all of it.
- But I can control him.

00:24.502 --> 00:26.330
- Well, that would take
some training.

00:26.374 --> 00:28.115
I know the perfect place.

00:28.158 --> 00:29.812
- Tom, this is Bill Hope--
Jillian's father.

00:29.855 --> 00:31.770
I just have something
very important to tell her

00:31.814 --> 00:34.730
about her family.
- Great, thank you.

00:34.773 --> 00:38.560
- Have a good night.

00:38.603 --> 00:39.822
Dad?

00:39.865 --> 00:42.738
- You leave
your sister alone.

00:42.781 --> 00:44.827
Stop it!
- [babbling]

00:44.870 --> 00:46.916
[grunting]

00:46.959 --> 00:49.353
[sinister music]

00:49.397 --> 00:51.442
[choking]

00:51.486 --> 00:54.489
[screams]

00:56.708 --> 00:58.754
[loon calling]

00:58.797 --> 01:01.757
[wind chimes tinkling]

01:01.800 --> 01:03.759
♪

01:03.802 --> 01:05.152
- All right.
Here we go.

01:05.195 --> 01:06.588
One more time, yeah?

01:06.631 --> 01:08.416
Baby steps.
Nothing too hard.

01:08.459 --> 01:10.461
Let's, uh...Let's start with
something simple.

01:10.505 --> 01:11.897
A rabbit.

01:11.941 --> 01:13.377
Just a cute little
bunny rabbit.

01:13.421 --> 01:14.596
Everybody likes bunnies,
right?

01:14.639 --> 01:16.380
That's an easy one.

01:16.424 --> 01:17.599
Now...

01:17.642 --> 01:20.254
Remember, picture it
in your mind.

01:20.297 --> 01:21.733
Attach a feeling.

01:21.777 --> 01:23.213
Comfort.

01:23.257 --> 01:25.215
Gratitude.

01:25.259 --> 01:27.304
Love.

01:27.348 --> 01:28.610
Imagine all of its parts.

01:28.653 --> 01:29.828
Imagine its--its whiskers;

01:29.872 --> 01:33.267
its eyes, its ears, nose.

01:33.310 --> 01:34.833
- [heart beating loudly, gasps]

01:34.877 --> 01:35.965
[breathing heavily]

01:36.008 --> 01:37.967
[panting]

01:38.010 --> 01:40.665
[groans, panting]

01:40.709 --> 01:42.841
Something feels different.

01:42.885 --> 01:44.582
[sighs]

01:44.626 --> 01:46.628
- Something is different.

01:46.671 --> 01:49.239
You lost part of yourself
yesterday,

01:49.283 --> 01:50.936
right?

01:50.980 --> 01:52.721
I remember when I lost
my first creation.

01:52.764 --> 01:55.506
It was fucking intense.

01:56.507 --> 01:58.727
I made him here, you know--

01:58.770 --> 02:00.729
this house--the first time.

02:00.772 --> 02:03.993
after drawing him
a million times.

02:04.036 --> 02:06.952
Oh, I used to love
to draw with my crayons.

02:06.996 --> 02:09.825
My first creation, Tall Boy,
he did some...

02:09.868 --> 02:11.783
not-so-great things
before I learned how

02:11.827 --> 02:13.437
to control him.

02:13.481 --> 02:15.918
But with practice,
you can learn not only

02:15.961 --> 02:18.616
to control them, but to--
to operate them, even.

02:18.660 --> 02:21.228
- What do you mean?
- Well, he can become

02:21.271 --> 02:23.534
sort of like your, uh,
puppet.

02:23.578 --> 02:26.798
It's--it's a special thing
that only you can do.

02:26.842 --> 02:28.496
You and me.

02:28.539 --> 02:29.845
It's cool. It's awesome!

02:29.888 --> 02:31.847
You know?
- [scoffs]

02:31.890 --> 02:33.327
- You're allowed to enjoy it.

02:33.370 --> 02:35.024
It's a superpower, right?

02:35.067 --> 02:36.852
You're just making
a bunny rabbit.

02:36.895 --> 02:38.506
- Okay.

02:38.549 --> 02:40.029
- This is the one.
You got this.

02:40.072 --> 02:42.814
Deep breath.
- [deep breathing]

02:42.858 --> 02:45.339
- Begin.

02:45.382 --> 02:47.819
[rising, intense music]

02:47.863 --> 02:50.996
- [breathing heavily]

02:51.040 --> 02:52.737
- Yeah, that's good.
That's great.

02:52.781 --> 02:54.522
♪

02:54.565 --> 02:55.523
[panting, groaning]
- Really good. Really good.

02:55.566 --> 02:56.915
Yeah.

02:56.959 --> 02:59.353
Picture all its parts.
Its eyes.

02:59.396 --> 03:01.529
Picture its ears,
its whiskers.

03:01.572 --> 03:03.879
- [panting]
- There you go, come on.

03:03.922 --> 03:05.750
[heart beating rapidly]

03:05.794 --> 03:07.012
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

03:07.056 --> 03:08.710
Almost, almost.

03:08.753 --> 03:10.059
Physical contact helps.
You ready?

03:10.102 --> 03:12.366
One, two, three.
Here we go.

03:12.409 --> 03:14.759
- [groaning, panting]

03:14.803 --> 03:17.762
[tense, psychedelic music]

03:17.806 --> 03:20.765
[heart beating rapidly]

03:20.809 --> 03:22.985
♪

03:23.028 --> 03:25.988
[heartbeat rising]

03:26.031 --> 03:28.425
[heart beat slows]

03:28.469 --> 03:30.732
- That was all you.

03:30.775 --> 03:33.256
I knew you could.

03:33.996 --> 03:36.433
Go on.

03:44.659 --> 03:47.096
Come on, let's see
that rabbit.

03:47.139 --> 03:50.317
- [shaky breathing]

04:12.382 --> 04:13.905
[dark music]

04:13.949 --> 04:16.908
[creature snarling]

04:16.952 --> 04:19.128
♪

04:19.171 --> 04:21.348
- Oh...
- Don't run away.

04:21.391 --> 04:22.958
Don't run away.

04:23.001 --> 04:25.439
[creature snarling]

04:25.482 --> 04:27.571
- [heavy breathing]

04:27.615 --> 04:30.574
[creature snarling]

04:30.618 --> 04:34.578
♪

04:34.622 --> 04:36.363
[breathing heavily]

04:36.406 --> 04:39.061
[creature snarling]

04:39.104 --> 04:40.497
[creature croaks]

04:42.456 --> 04:44.066
- Ugh.

04:44.109 --> 04:45.546
- [groans]

04:45.589 --> 04:47.156
- Well, they can't all
be winners.

04:47.199 --> 04:49.854
♪

04:49.898 --> 04:51.639
Like your dog, you know.

04:51.682 --> 04:54.119
It took me a bunch of tries
to get that one right.

04:54.163 --> 04:55.730
♪

04:55.773 --> 04:57.775
- My dog?

04:57.819 --> 04:59.647
You made my dog?

04:59.690 --> 05:01.170
- Yeah.

05:01.213 --> 05:02.780
You were moving in,
and I thought

05:02.824 --> 05:04.913
I'd send you a little present.

05:04.956 --> 05:06.393
♪

05:06.436 --> 05:08.003
Eww.

05:08.046 --> 05:15.053
♪

05:18.883 --> 05:21.016
Hey.
- Hey.

05:25.890 --> 05:27.718
I thought I left my phone
in my purse.

05:30.504 --> 05:32.201
Shit.

05:32.244 --> 05:35.944
[eggs sizzling]

05:35.987 --> 05:38.207
It's dead.

05:38.250 --> 05:41.123
I've never broken
a phone before in my life.

05:41.166 --> 05:42.820
- Well, if only
a cracked screen

05:42.864 --> 05:44.605
were your biggest problem
right now.

05:44.648 --> 05:45.736
[laughs]
Right?

05:50.088 --> 05:52.090
- I think I need some air.
- Yeah.

05:52.134 --> 05:54.049
Yeah, sure.

05:54.092 --> 06:00.838
♪

06:02.623 --> 06:05.669
[line trilling]

06:07.454 --> 06:10.457
[line continues trilling]

06:10.500 --> 06:12.067
♪

06:12.110 --> 06:13.895
- Hey, this is Jill.
Leave a message.

06:13.938 --> 06:15.026
[voicemail beeps]

06:15.070 --> 06:16.245
- [sighs]

06:16.288 --> 06:18.116
Hey, um...

06:18.160 --> 06:19.422
it's me.

06:22.251 --> 06:23.948
I don't know where you are.

06:26.211 --> 06:28.736
Or if you're with...

06:28.779 --> 06:29.737
him.

06:29.780 --> 06:31.521
[clears throat]

06:31.565 --> 06:34.219
[melancholy music]

06:34.263 --> 06:36.657
I just don't know, Jill.

06:36.700 --> 06:38.746
[sighs]

06:38.789 --> 06:42.097
♪

06:42.140 --> 06:44.142
Please come home.

06:44.186 --> 06:48.799
♪

06:48.843 --> 06:51.802
[chimes ringing]

06:51.846 --> 06:55.763
♪

06:55.806 --> 06:58.287
[dog panting]
Hey.

06:58.330 --> 06:59.593
♪

06:59.636 --> 07:01.246
[whispering indistinctly]

07:01.290 --> 07:03.118
[kissing]

07:03.161 --> 07:05.599
Yes. Yes.

07:05.642 --> 07:07.165
[groans]
I need you right now.

07:07.209 --> 07:09.733
You miss her, too.

07:09.777 --> 07:10.734
[dog sneezes]

07:10.778 --> 07:12.519
Oh.

07:12.562 --> 07:14.608
Yep.

07:16.305 --> 07:19.308
[dog panting]

07:19.351 --> 07:21.615
[chimes ringing]

07:21.658 --> 07:23.660
[dog panting]

07:23.704 --> 07:26.663
[quiet, tense music]

07:26.707 --> 07:30.275
♪

07:30.319 --> 07:33.278
[foreboding music]

07:33.322 --> 07:39.633
♪

07:39.676 --> 07:42.636
[chimes ringing]

07:42.679 --> 07:49.686
♪

07:57.694 --> 08:00.697
[low growling]

08:09.227 --> 08:12.187
[suspenseful music]

08:12.230 --> 08:14.711
♪

08:15.886 --> 08:17.018
[low growl]

08:24.286 --> 08:26.897
[low growling]

08:40.345 --> 08:42.347
[low panting]

08:42.391 --> 08:45.699
[distant barking]

08:45.742 --> 08:52.706
♪

08:52.749 --> 08:54.229
[loon calls]

08:54.272 --> 08:56.840
[wind chimes ringing]

08:56.884 --> 08:58.363
- [quietly] Hey.

08:58.407 --> 08:59.408
Hey, where you going?

08:59.451 --> 09:02.890
♪

09:02.933 --> 09:04.892
Oh.

09:04.935 --> 09:07.155
You want to go
into Ian's house, huh?

09:07.198 --> 09:08.243
♪

09:08.286 --> 09:09.723
[sighs]
Okay.

09:09.766 --> 09:14.379
♪

09:14.423 --> 09:15.903
[door clicks open]

09:17.469 --> 09:19.384
Ian?

09:19.428 --> 09:26.609
♪

09:34.095 --> 09:35.226
Ian?

09:35.270 --> 09:41.406
♪

09:41.450 --> 09:43.452
- Ian?

09:43.495 --> 09:50.677
♪

09:52.461 --> 09:55.029
[birds chirping]

09:55.072 --> 09:59.903
♪

09:59.947 --> 10:01.949
[wind chimes ringing]

10:01.992 --> 10:05.953
♪

10:05.996 --> 10:07.911
[low growling]

10:07.955 --> 10:14.962
♪

10:18.443 --> 10:21.664
[screen door creaks]

10:23.361 --> 10:25.102
[door slams]

10:25.146 --> 10:27.801
♪

10:27.844 --> 10:28.976
Ian?

10:29.019 --> 10:31.979
[wind chimes continue ringing]

10:32.022 --> 10:36.897
♪

10:36.940 --> 10:38.681
[door creaks, thuds shut]

10:43.338 --> 10:44.469
[door creaks]

10:44.513 --> 10:47.472
[foreboding music]

10:47.516 --> 10:54.697
♪

10:56.481 --> 10:58.266
[low panting]

10:58.309 --> 11:00.834
♪

11:00.877 --> 11:03.053
[dog whines, pants]

11:03.097 --> 11:06.056
[rising tense music]

11:06.100 --> 11:13.063
♪

11:13.107 --> 11:15.065
[music builds]

11:15.109 --> 11:22.116
♪

11:23.595 --> 11:25.467
- [sighs]

11:25.510 --> 11:28.078
[laughs]

11:45.139 --> 11:48.142
[foreboding music]

11:48.185 --> 11:55.192
♪

11:56.019 --> 11:58.065
- Breakfast is ready.

11:58.108 --> 12:01.068
♪

12:01.111 --> 12:02.939
Hey, Jill?

12:02.983 --> 12:09.990
♪

12:12.557 --> 12:14.429
Hey, Jill?

12:14.472 --> 12:17.432
[dark music]

12:17.475 --> 12:20.435
[dishes clattering]

12:20.478 --> 12:27.485
♪

12:31.968 --> 12:34.275
- Hey.

12:34.318 --> 12:35.972
Smells delicious.

12:39.019 --> 12:39.236
.

12:39.280 --> 12:40.498
- [sniffs]

12:44.459 --> 12:45.982
[sniffs]

12:49.029 --> 12:50.073
[sniffs]

12:52.859 --> 12:53.990
[sighs]

12:54.034 --> 12:56.471
♪

12:56.514 --> 12:59.474
[sinister music]

12:59.517 --> 13:03.434
♪

13:03.478 --> 13:05.959
What the fuck?

13:06.002 --> 13:13.009
♪

13:33.203 --> 13:36.250
[boxes clattering]

13:36.293 --> 13:39.253
[dark, curious music]

13:39.296 --> 13:46.303
♪

14:00.404 --> 14:02.406
- I have a question.

14:02.450 --> 14:05.540
- Mm-hmm?
- You said you made the dog.

14:05.583 --> 14:07.020
[tense music]

14:07.063 --> 14:09.631
Why did you choose
that particular dog?

14:09.674 --> 14:10.632
♪

14:10.675 --> 14:13.330
- Um...

14:13.374 --> 14:14.549
Well, you know, I--
I don't know.

14:14.592 --> 14:15.593
[nervous laugh]

14:15.637 --> 14:17.987
♪

14:18.031 --> 14:19.684
- It's just, um--

14:19.728 --> 14:22.078
it's just so funny,

14:22.122 --> 14:24.689
I had a stuffed animal
that looked just like that

14:24.733 --> 14:26.735
when I was really little.

14:26.778 --> 14:28.389
♪

14:28.432 --> 14:30.173
- Weird.

14:30.217 --> 14:33.394
♪

14:33.437 --> 14:35.222
- [laughs]

14:35.265 --> 14:42.272
♪

14:43.230 --> 14:46.233
[foreboding music]

14:46.276 --> 14:53.283
♪

14:55.982 --> 14:58.985
[sinister music]

14:59.028 --> 15:06.035
♪

15:22.312 --> 15:25.054
- What was your mom like?

15:29.798 --> 15:31.582
- My mom?

15:31.626 --> 15:33.149
Why?

15:33.193 --> 15:34.542
[tense music]

15:34.585 --> 15:36.196
- Just...

15:36.239 --> 15:38.546
curious to know more
about you.

15:38.589 --> 15:45.553
♪

15:45.596 --> 15:48.077
- She passed away.

15:48.121 --> 15:54.562
♪

15:54.605 --> 15:56.520
- I'm so sorry.
- Yeah, yeah.

15:56.564 --> 15:58.653
Earlier this year.

16:02.309 --> 16:05.268
She was, um...

16:05.312 --> 16:07.357
she was very trusting.

16:07.401 --> 16:08.576
♪

16:08.619 --> 16:10.143
That was her weakness,
probably.

16:10.186 --> 16:12.449
She was too trusting.

16:12.493 --> 16:15.800
She saw the world the way
she wanted to see it.

16:15.844 --> 16:17.498
Well...

16:17.541 --> 16:19.804
the way her husband
told her to see it.

16:19.848 --> 16:23.330
♪

16:23.373 --> 16:28.074
I think she chose
not to see certain things.

16:28.117 --> 16:29.814
♪

16:29.858 --> 16:31.294
You can do that,
you know...

16:31.338 --> 16:32.600
♪

16:32.643 --> 16:35.168
Make your own reality.

16:35.211 --> 16:39.302
♪

16:39.346 --> 16:41.304
But she really loved me,
you know?

16:41.348 --> 16:43.524
Like--like, whoa.

16:43.567 --> 16:46.744
♪

16:46.788 --> 16:48.355
She never understood me,
but she--

16:48.398 --> 16:49.834
but she--she kept trying.

16:49.878 --> 16:52.620
She never stopped,
and she really...

16:52.663 --> 16:54.317
deserved...

16:54.361 --> 16:56.885
better than she got.

16:56.928 --> 17:02.282
♪

17:02.325 --> 17:04.588
[gulps]

17:04.632 --> 17:11.639
♪

17:14.381 --> 17:17.384
[smacking, crunching]

17:17.427 --> 17:19.734
♪

17:19.777 --> 17:22.128
[swallows loudly]

17:22.171 --> 17:23.912
You okay?

17:23.955 --> 17:28.743
♪

17:28.786 --> 17:30.658
- I think I need to go home.

17:30.701 --> 17:32.747
♪

17:32.790 --> 17:34.618
- Yeah, okay.

17:37.317 --> 17:37.534
.

17:37.578 --> 17:40.711
[engine rumbling]

17:41.538 --> 17:43.758
[foreboding music]

17:43.801 --> 17:50.765
♪

17:50.808 --> 17:54.247
- We don't have
to go back now, you know.

17:54.290 --> 17:55.596
I mean it might not even--

17:55.639 --> 17:57.206
might not be the best thing

17:57.250 --> 17:59.513
for your training, you know?

17:59.556 --> 18:01.819
Doing really good.

18:01.863 --> 18:05.258
[foreboding music continues]

18:05.301 --> 18:11.655
♪

18:15.790 --> 18:22.840
♪

18:39.379 --> 18:40.815
[sinister music]

18:40.858 --> 18:43.513
- Did you see that?
- Someone's in my house.

18:43.557 --> 18:47.387
♪

18:47.430 --> 18:49.998
[car doors squeak]

18:50.041 --> 18:57.223
♪

19:20.463 --> 19:21.725
Hey, Tom.

19:23.814 --> 19:26.034
You, uh...

19:26.077 --> 19:29.516
you looking for something, man?

19:29.559 --> 19:31.779
- Why were you at the motel
last night?

19:31.822 --> 19:33.868
- What?

19:33.911 --> 19:36.392
- I saw you at the motel.

19:36.436 --> 19:38.264
- I wasn't at any motel
last night, man.

19:38.307 --> 19:40.396
I was--I was with Jillian.

19:40.440 --> 19:42.659
All night.
- What motel?

19:42.703 --> 19:45.749
What time?
- I was with you.

19:45.793 --> 19:48.491
- I was asleep.

19:48.535 --> 19:50.885
- Your dad called me.

19:50.928 --> 19:53.931
♪

19:53.975 --> 19:55.498
- What?
- He said he needed

19:55.542 --> 19:56.978
to talk to you
about something urgent.

19:57.021 --> 19:59.328
About your family.

19:59.372 --> 20:01.635
That he couldn't reach you.

20:01.678 --> 20:03.332
♪

20:03.376 --> 20:05.856
So I went to go meet him
at that motel off of 270,

20:05.900 --> 20:09.077
and when I got there
this guy, he was leaving

20:09.120 --> 20:10.948
and your dad was nowhere
to be found.

20:10.992 --> 20:13.734
So where is her dad?

20:13.777 --> 20:16.389
Why were you at that motel?

20:16.432 --> 20:18.086
Why you got all these pictures
of her?

20:18.129 --> 20:20.349
- Man, I...

20:20.393 --> 20:22.525
look, I--I mean, I don't
even know where to start.

20:22.569 --> 20:24.919
This is--
is fucking insane, man.

20:24.962 --> 20:27.574
[muffled speech]

20:27.617 --> 20:30.098
[tense music]

20:30.141 --> 20:32.535
[inaudible speech]

20:32.579 --> 20:36.452
♪

20:36.496 --> 20:38.933
What?

20:38.976 --> 20:41.065
- I know who you are.

20:41.109 --> 20:46.114
♪

20:46.157 --> 20:48.464
- Yeah.
[laughs]

20:49.987 --> 20:53.034
- Okay, what are y'all
talking about?

20:53.077 --> 20:55.776
- He must have bought
the place later on, right?

20:55.819 --> 20:58.431
[quiet, brooding music]

20:58.474 --> 21:01.869
He took me and my mom there
a few times as well.

21:01.912 --> 21:05.002
Weekends at the lake.

21:05.046 --> 21:07.744
I was almost too young
to even remember it.

21:07.788 --> 21:10.138
- I was wondering if you would.

21:10.181 --> 21:11.966
♪

21:12.009 --> 21:14.490
- I left that little
stuffed dog there, as well.

21:14.534 --> 21:16.579
Didn't I?

21:16.623 --> 21:19.408
- What are you talking about?

21:19.452 --> 21:21.802
- He's my brother.

21:21.845 --> 21:23.717
- Half-brother.

21:23.760 --> 21:26.807
[dark, revelatory music]

21:26.850 --> 21:27.982
